Date: Wed, 28 Mar 2018 09:50:37 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 210/210] arm: dts: am572x-idk-pps: add ptp_bc pps
 output-selection gpios

A gpio-controlled multiplexer is added to guarantee that there is only
one PPS output at any time at the AM571(2)x-idk.

This patch add PTP_BC-controlled gpio entries

Signed-off-by: Eric Ruei <e-ruei1@ti.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/am572x-idk-pps.dts | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am572x-idk-pps.dts b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am572x-idk-pps.dts
index 0ba906e..4bbab9c 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am572x-idk-pps.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am572x-idk-pps.dts
@@ -110,5 +110,8 @@
 };
 
 &ptp_bc {
+	pps-sel0-gpios = <&gpio1 4 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
+	pps-sel1-gpios = <&gpio6 7 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
+
 	status = "okay";
 };
